The importing data progress indicator is nice, but the esitmation process is off by quite a bit.  Seems to do ok with the initial import process but then gets off track with the "apply special processing" and the portion after that (forget the text).

For example, after a few minutes the estimate settled down to about 30 minutes and I believe the initial import process completed in about that time.  Then the special processing kicked in and then gradually the estimate kept moving up to about 50-55 minutes total.  Got down to about 1 minute left.  Then after special processing was finished, jumped back up to 6 minutes left.  Total import finished in 59 minutes.

Entering rich text mode consistently unescapes the '@' symbol in wiki pages.  This is verified by making wiki markup mode default, then editing a page containing: 

{noformat} \[fax:\@company\@1+areacode+7digitnumber\] {noformat}

It's the correct markup source while in wiki markup mode, but as soon as i switch to rich text and back to wiki markup (NO OTHER ACTION ON MY PART) it becomes this:

{noformat}  \[fax:@company@1+areacode+7digitnumber\] {noformat}

users defaulting to rich text will never know its happening as it's 'behind-the-scenes',  it's very frustrating destroying formatting unrelated to a change they might be making elsewhere in the page.

This umbrella issue covers markup bugs caused by switching between wiki markup, rich text and the rendered page.

